('28', '62', '15/03 The service was done but we didn\'t have the spark plugs in stock, we ordered and the parts arrived today, he brought the bike to change\r\nAll ready', '2025-03-15 13:01:39', '2025-03-15 13:01:39'),
('32', '65', 'Notes: The indicator buttons is broken, but working \r\n\r\n\r\n MOT £29.65 - MOT PAID RECEIPT 1052\r\n\r\nFor pass in MOT need fixe the following things:\r\n\r\n-Left indicator not working\r\n-Horn is not Working\r\n-Light of the plate is not working\r\n\r\n\r\nPrices: \r\n-If is only new horn, only £25 \r\n-We don\'t have that light plate, if is only eletric problem £30 \r\n-If we have and if is only the left light indicator £10, if the problem is in the indicator need change the both indicator,\r\nwe have only oxford indicator EL337(£20) price only the parts plus £30 for fixe \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe customer will leave the bike for fixe the problem  and make MOT for tomorrow 18/03/2025\r\n\r\nPlease confirm this message, if you agree!\r\n\r\nGustavo', '2025-03-18 17:57:14', '2025-03-18 17:57:14'),
('33', '65', 'After inspecting your motorcycle, we have identified the following issues:\r\n\r\nIndicator Light: The indicator light is LED, and due to its design, it cannot be repaired and will need to be replaced with a new one.\r\n\r\nHorn : The issue lies with the horn, which needs to be replaced. The cost of the new part is £15, and the installation is £10.\r\n\r\nLicense Plate Light: The LED license plate light is damaged and requires replacement. Unfortunately, we do not have an identical or original part. However, we can replace the lamp holder for the plate, which will allow it to function correctly and pass the MOT.\r\n\r\nSummary of parts and services required:\r\n\r\nReplacement of the indicator light (LED) - Parts £20 and labour £30\r\nReplacement of the horn – Part: £15, Installation: £10\r\nReplacement of the license plate light – Replacement of the lamp holder - for a normal light (not led) with suport - £30 \r\n\r\nTotal estimated cost:  £105\r\n\r\nPlease confirm if you authorize the replacement of all the parts and services mentioned so we can proceed with the work.\r\n\r\nWe look forward to your confirmation.', '2025-03-18 17:57:14', '2025-03-18 17:57:14'),
('34', '66', 'PARTS NOT IN STOCK, THERE IS A 4 WEEKS WAIT FOR THEM.', '2025-03-20 13:31:30', '2025-03-20 13:31:30'),
('35', '64', 'Service Report - Customer\'s Motorcycle\r\n\r\nDate of Arrival: 17/03 at 18:15\r\n\r\nCustomer\'s Request : The customer reported the following issues with the motorcycle:\r\n\r\nOil Change and Rear Brake Light Bulb Replacement : The customer requested an oil change and replacement of the rear brake light bulb.\r\n\r\nStarting Issue: The customer mentioned that the motorcycle is not starting after hitting a curb with the jack. Some wires were broken due to the impact, which seems to be causing the starting issue.\r\n\r\nEngine Stalling : The customer noted that when the motorcycle was parked, the engine stopped running. This issue needs to be investigated.\r\n\r\nMOT Test : The customer also requested the motorcycle to be checked for the MOT (mandatory vehicle inspection in the UK) to ensure it passes the inspection.\r\n\r\nCondition of the Motorcycle Upon Arrival : Upon arrival at the workshop on 17/03 at 18:15, the motorcycle was not starting and displayed visible defects in certain parts. The customer also provided a video showing the condition of the motorcycle when it was delivered.\r\n\r\nInitial Actions Required :\r\n\r\nAttempt to Start the Motorcycle : First, we will attempt to start the motorcycle to assess the cause of the starting issue.\r\n\r\nElectrical Inspection: If the problem is related to the electrical system, a full inspection of the wiring and components will be necessary. This electrical inspection will be charged separately at a rate of £80 to thoroughly check the motorcycle and identify any issues with wires or electrical components.\r\n\r\nMOT Checklist : After checking the motorcycle\'s functionality, a detailed checklist will be performed to ensure the motorcycle meets the requirements to pass the MOT. This will include checking essential components such as lighting system, brakes, tires, and other necessary items.\r\n\r\nAgreement with the Customer:\r\n\r\nThe customer has been informed that the initial diagnosis of the motorcycle will proceed as described above. The electrical inspection fee of £80 will apply, and the MOT checklist will be performed afterward. The customer is aware that we cannot guarantee the motorcycle will be ready for pickup on 18/03, as it will depend on the assessment and any necessary repairs.\r\n\r\nThe customer has confirmed that they agree with the outlined procedures and has authorized the start of the work.\r\n\r\nConfirm this message if you agree with the services\r\n\r\nLet me know if you need any further adjustments!', '2025-03-25 17:21:46', '2025-03-25 17:21:46'),
('37', '58', 'During the Basic service inspection, it was noted that the Rear Brake Pads are worn and require replacement.\r\nEBC Brake Pads – £25\r\nYamaha Brake Pads – £35', '2025-03-27 16:41:09', '2025-03-27 16:41:09'),
('38', '53', 'Mechanics managed to start your vehicle; however, a significant noise was coming from the engine. A video of the issue was shared with you for reference.\r\n\r\nTo investigate further, we dismantled the clutch, variator, and belt kit to check for any additional damage. During the inspection, we found that the Kit Belt and Air Filter needed replacement.\r\n\r\nAfter receiving your confirmation, we replaced the necessary components. The vehicle was then reassembled and left running for 30 minutes to ensure everything was functioning correctly.\r\n\r\nPlease drive a maximum of 300 miles and then bring the vehicle back to us for a follow-up inspection. At that stage, we will also check the coolant to ensure the water pump is in good condition.', '2025-03-27 16:41:44', '2025-03-27 16:41:44'),
('41', '68', 'During the service, mechanic Luiz reported that several lights on the motorcycle are not working (burnt out). Additionally, the bike is showing starting issues. The mechanic is currently diagnosing the root cause of the problem.', '2025-03-29 12:54:03', '2025-03-29 12:54:03'),
